		spouse'. Canon 1055. ssmm. Canon 209. </span></p>
				<p style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</p>
				<p style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Times New Roman; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
				<font face="Arial">&nbsp;• Peters' Blog, 14 oct 2014 (2),&nbsp;<a target="_blank" style="text-decoration: none;" href="https://canonlawblog.wordpress.com/2014/10/14/a-note-on-relatio-post-disceptationem-51/">here</a>.&nbsp;</font><span class="z3988" span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; font-family: Arial;">&#9642; 
				Relatio post disceptationem 51, asserting that same-sex unions 
				are not on the same footing as marriage, is so platitudinistic 
				as to be alarming. &gt; Canon 1055. '</span><font face="Arial">Same-sex 
				marriage'</font><span class="z3988" span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; font-family: Arial;">. 
				Synod. Marriage. Infallibility.</span></p>
				<p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;<p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
		<font face="Arial">&nbsp;• Peters' Blog, 27 mar 2013,
		<a target="_blank" href="https://canonlawblog.wordpress.com/2013/03/27/a-primer-on-church-teaching-regarding-same-sex-marriage/">
		here</a>. </font>
		<span class="z3988"
		span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; font-family: Arial">
		&#9642; A primer on Church teaching regarding ssmm; CDF's Considerations 
		confused same-sex union with ssmm. &gt; Canon 1055. Infallibility.</span></p>
				<p style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
				&nbsp;</p>
				<p style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Times New Roman; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
				<font face="Arial">&nbsp;• Peters' Blog, 21 nov 2008 (1),&nbsp;<a target="_blank" style="text-decoration: none;" href="https://canonlawblog.wordpress.com/2008/11/21/same-sex-marriage-in-medieval-canon-law/">here</a>. 
				Noting that, in a rare medieval mention of the topic, Hostiensis 
				expressly ejects marriage attempted between two persons of the 
				same sex. &gt; Canon 1055.&nbsp;</font><span class="z3988" span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; font-family: Arial;">'</span><font face="Arial">Same-sex 
				marriage'. Decretal Law.</font></p>
				<p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
		&nbsp;</p>
				<p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;<p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
		&nbsp;<p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
		&nbsp;<p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
		&nbsp;<p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
		<font face="Arial"><span style="background-color: #EEECE1">
		&nbsp;Divorce-and-civil-remarriage among Catholics</span>.</font><p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
		&nbsp;<p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
		&nbsp;<p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
		&nbsp;</td>
	</tr>
</table>
